Combine flour, salt and pepper in shallow dish. Dip chicken in eggs, then flour mixture; set aside. Melt 1-1/2 tablespoons I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!(R) Cooking & Baking sticks in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and brown chicken in batches; set aside. Stir lemon juice, then broth into same skillet. Bring to a boil over high heat. Return chicken to skillet. Reduce heat to low and simmer 3 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Stir in remaining 6 tablespoons Spread until melted, then sprinkle with parsley.